settings.title: What’s the difference?
settings.subheading1:
Hemp has always been a popular ingredient in skin care and even clothing, but the health benefits of ingestion are innumerable and best of all – no prescription is required.  
Available in the health food section of many supermarkets, products such as hemp seeds, protein powders and oil has in recent times been touted as the latest health superfood.  
Low in calories and high in plant-based Omega-3, ingestible hemp has been legal since 2016.
settings.subheading2:
CBD or cannabidiol is another compound found in cannabis that is not psychoactive. CBD is thought to be responsible for the majority of medical benefits, such as pain, stress and anxiety relief, a reduction of inflammation and the suppression of muscle spasms.
CBD may also help in the treatment of OCD, depression, low blood sugar, seizures, joint damage, glaucoma and many more medical conditions.
settings.subheading3:
THC is most known for its psychoactive side effect, which can produce a sense of euphoria or a ‘high’ in users. It can assist with sleep, suppress muscle spasms, alleviate pain and reduce nausea.
It is important to discuss your needs closely with your doctor to ensure you receive the correct dosage and cannabis strain and strength.

settings.title: Mental Health
settings.text: Mental health conditions are often treated with pharmaceutical drugs which usually have a number of side effects including insomnia, headache and drowsiness. Research shows that some mental health disorders such as anxiety, stress, depression, PTSD can be benefited by the use of plant based alternatives without the negative side effects from traditional medicines. Endocannabinoid and Plant based medicines have been shown to help regulate the system that causes fear and anxiety in the body and brain.

settings.title: Chronic Pain
settings.text: One of the most widely popular uses for endocannabinoid medicines is for pain management. Patients are increasingly searching for an alternative to traditional pain-relieving medications, including painkillers and opioids, to help manage their symptoms. Research shows alternative medicines may ease certain types of chronic pain, including pain resulting from nerve damage and inflammation, improving patients quality of life without causing serious side effects.

settings.title: Gut Health
settings.text: Some research suggests that endocannabinoid medicines may play a role in achieving good gut health. In particular, inflammatory bowel disease (IBD), Crohn’s disease and ulcerative colitis, might be positively influenced in part by endocannabinoid treatment which might modulate inflammatory responses. Plant based medicines can also assist with appetite stimulation and help to reduce nausea and vomiting.

settings.title: Sleep
settings.text: There are many plant based treatments used as a sleep aid that have been shown to reduce the symptoms of insomnia, increase the onset of sleep and increase the overall duration of sleep without causing the patients to feel excessively tired the next day.

settings.title: Anxiety
settings.text: Plant based treatments and endocannabinoid medicine can alleviate anxiety by activating certain biological receptors and pathways associated with adenosine and serotonin. It can also slow and reduce the uptake of beneficial chemicals like serotonin, dopamine and GABA, allowing our bodies to use these naturally produced chemicals for a more sustained period of time.

settings.title: Cancer Symptoms
settings.text: Studies have shown that there are possible benefits of endocannaboid medicine on relieving cancer symptoms and treatment side effects. This includes alleviating nausea and vomiting for patients undergoing chemotherapy and assisting with cancer-related pain by cannabinoid receptors in the brain and other parts of the body. Nerve pain as a result of chemotherapy or other traditional cancer treatments may also be effectively treated and there are some studies that show that plant based alternatives may also help improve appetite for people with cancer.

settings.title: Neurological
settings.text:
Plant based medicines are thought to help support healthy brain function and encourages neurogenesis. They can assist in the reduction of neurodegeneration as some are an antioxidant, which is also neuroprotective and antipsychotic. 

Due to its ability to reduce muscle spasms and seizures, more and more researchers are conducting studies into the treatment benefits of endocannabinoid medicines on those with Epilepsy.

settings.title: Migranes
settings.text: Migraines are very common with more than 80% of people experiencing migraines before the age of 35. Some people find that their headaches can lead to migraines and if they are frequent, over the counter medicines simply do not work after prolonged use. Plant based alternatives are used to treat migraines if traditional migraine medications are no longer helping with patients sometimes seeing a drop in the frequency and severity of their migraines.

settings.title: Chronic Illness
settings.text: Endocannabinoid medicines have great potential as an analgesic and can be beneficial in relieving a patients ongoing pain and therefore can provide relief to patients living with Chronic illnesses. Suffering a chronic illness effects a patients quality of life and often have multiple and complex causes. Plant based medicines are a great alternative to pain medications and opioids when managing chronic pain. Some common chronic illnesses include Fibromyalgia, Arthritis and Multiple Sclerosis.

settings.title: Palliative Care
settings.text: Living with a terminal or life-threatening disease is extremely challenging for patients and studies have shown that endocannabinoid medicines may have a therapeutic effect. They can be used to help to alleviate some of a patients symptoms and including nausea as well as physical and psychosocial  pain.

settings.title: Quit Smoking
settings.text: Studies suggest that endocannabidiol medicines can aid in helping a patient quit smoking for good. Symptoms of nicotine withdrawal can vary from person to person and often can deter a person from quitting smoking. These can include a lack of concentration, anger management issues and/or anxious behaviour with disruptions in your sleep pattern, and sudden weight gain. Plant based medicines help patients to relax and contribute to increasing will power, mental strength and decreasing pain which in turn, helps a patient with the management of nicotine withdrawal.

settings.about_left_pera_fourth:
Greencare Clinics is a health services company comprising a team of authorized specialist physicians and nurses who provide premium healthcare advice and support for patients when accessing legal Plant Based and Endocannabinoid medicines.

At Greencare, our goal is to support patients in accessing legal Plant Based and Endocannabinoid medicines as an effective plant based medical treatment, when other treatments have failed them. We believe in providing people with alternative treatments to help them on their wellness journey.

We aim to work with our patients to assist them in achieving long term health goals based upon their personal needs and conditions.

Our focus is on safe and controlled administration, we thoroughly pre-screen our patients to optimise a treatment plan, specifically tailored for them. We monitor our patients closely post appointments for any potential adverse events while working towards positive outcomes.

Greencare’s specialist team of physicians provides patients with ongoing support and communication throughout the process in order for our patients to feel confident when utilizing this new form of medical treatment.

Our team are experts in the field of legal Plant Based and Endocannabinoid medicines and are registered Authorised Prescribers with the TGA.
settings.about_left_pera_five:
Greencare’s founder was first exposed to the world of plant based alternatives and endocannabinoid medicines when a friend who was suffering with cancer, found great benefit managing their pain and nausea whilst using the medicines. A family member suffering from Fibromyalgia had seen significantly positive results and personally he also found great relief with his own struggle with insomnia thanks to the medicines prescribed.

Since seeing these initial benefits, Greencare’s founder consulted with practicing medical doctors, leading experts and advocates in the field of plant based medicine and found himself wishing to share the opportunity and expertise of these people to the wider Australian community.

Hoping to benefit as many people as possible through a more natural approach to health care, Greencare Clinics was created to provide a naturally derived alternative to traditional medicines to manage your health.
